== Research Experience
*Summer Interniship*\n
/Pennsylvania State University/\n
April 2021 - Present\n

We are working on the project of multilingual semantic parsing, which involves turning sentences in multiple natural languages to logical forms, such as, SQL, Prolog, and Funql.\n

- Processed the data for the seq2seqPtr model on multilingual semantic parsing
- Currently running the OpenNMT model on different datasets for baseline multilingual semantic parsing \n\n

*Research Assistant*\n
/Knowledge and Wisdom Lab at Xi'an Jiaotong-Liverpool University/\n
October 2020 - Present\n

We are developing an intelligent policy management system which provides services such as policy queries and policy analysis. We work on this project in collaboration with China Telecom, Beijing.\n

- Developed the backend of an intelligent policy management system using Python
- Realized the inverted index based on whoosh for policy searching with data stored in MongoDB
- Extracted keywords of policy documents and used word cloud to visualize the results
- Extracted the topics of policy documents using LDA model
- Currently working on the relation extraction using GCN

== Work Experience
*NLP Engineer Internship*\n
/Shanghai Ideal Information Industry(Group) Co.,Ltd/\n
June 2020 – September 2020\n

During this internship, I worked in the center of research and developement at IDEAL, which was repsonsible for the 12345 hotline service in Shanghai. I explored some traditional techniques to complete some NLP tasks and provided analysis of ticket data.\n

- Classified tickets into predefined scenes using text similarity techniques
- Developed a web page for question and answering using text similarity techniques
- Developed a web page for keyword extraction offering 3 methods: TF-IDF, word2vec and chi squared test
- Explored Named Entity Recognition tasks using CRF and BERT-MRC \n\n

*Frontend Developer Internship*\n
/Emerson Electric (China) Holdings Co., Ltd./\n
July 2020 – September 2020\n

During this internship, I led a team to develop a Wechar mini program for Emerson to collect feedback from its customers and manage database. I mainly focuses on the frontend development and project management.\n

- Developed the frontend of a Wechat mini program using Wechat Devtools
- Assigned work to members and led the team to work on the project following the schedule

